This paper discusses the use of deep neural networks and their explanation methods, which are commonly studied in the fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of these methods in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) applications. Additionally, the paper discusses the challenges posed by complex and evolving neural network structures, which could fall under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR).
